CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 16, 1966, pg. 1B reads:"Young Set Have Fun Too At Alpha Dance - Between Sets - The Student Union of the University of Pittsburgh was the scene of youthful gaiety when Alpha Phi Alpha Fraternity sponsored a benefit dance for the United Negro College Fund. It was under the supervision of the UNCF's Women's Division, headed by Miss Nancy Lee...Pretty, Pretties - Barbara Ewing and Mabel Singleton were among the pretty girls attending the Alpha's benefit dance at the University of Pitstburgh's Student Union recently.  The girls are popular members of the smart young set."
TitMainTitle: Barbara Ewing and Mabel Singleton, posed in University of Pittsburgh Student Union for Alpha Phi Alpha benefit dance for United Negro College Fund
